$interpreted: Tapir Chieftain: Hope, trial, goes well, select, suitable arbiter.
Yao: Don't worry, everything will go just fine.
Tapir Chieftain: You! Why, awake? Drink, Dream Broth...
Yao: I didn't swallow it.
Yao: And now, the moment I've been waiting for.
Yao: I can uproot this corruption at the source!
Tapir Chieftain: What is, your plan? Stay where, you are! The Udumbara, left behind, sacred tool...
Yao: Sacred! Why!? Just because it sparked an Alliance that's just as hollow as your rotten old tree!?
Tapir Chieftain: Quick, stop him!
Tapir Guard: Don't let him get away!
Yao: Stop me!? Are you kidding!?
Yao: I've been preparing for this day for a long, long time! Just you try and stop me!
Yao: Come on, let's see what you've got!
Tapir Chieftain: H-How...!?
Yao: Now you're the only one left.
Tapir Chieftain: R-Retreat.
Tapir Chieftain: Yagh!
Yao: Eh?
Remaining Tapir: Chieftain, go get help!
Yao: Get out of here!
Tapir Chieftain: (Get help... but he's blocking the door...)
Tapir Chieftain: (Dream Flower! The way, passed down from the Keeper of the Udumbara!)
Tapir Chieftain: Please, reach, contestants...
Pang: ...If we're here together as part of the trial, then... where is Yao?
Tindoiimu: Who knows? Making he's having his trial somewhere else. Anything could happen here...
Pang: Hmm...
Tindoiimu: Eh?
Tindoiimu: It's you!?
Pang: Watch out, I think this dream is changing!
Pang: Thank you.
Tindoiimu: Don't thank me, I don't owe you anything.
???: Kindness of the soul, can make one greater than themselves.
Pang: It's the Keeper of the Udumbara again...
???: And yet... Saving lives, or saving the world... Two ideals at odds. How to decide---
Pang: What in the...!?
Pang: Yao!?
Pang: Stop!!
Tindoiimu: Don't waste your strength. We're in a dream, remember?
???: Dream, reality... reality, dream... dream, reality...
Pang: Wait a second... is that the Tapir Chieftain!?
Tindoiimu: It's another pathway?
???: Awake from dreams, save the dying, oh valiant warrior...
???: Continue in dreams, stable, just, oh righteous master.
Tindoiimu: Where are you going?
Pang: Something doesn't feel right... I think something might be amiss in the waking world!
Tindoiimu: Didn't you hear what that voice said? Forward is the path to righteousness. This might be the way to become arbiter.
Tindoiimu: You're going to give all that up for some illusion?
Pang: If being arbiter means I have to ignore when someone is in need, then I'd rather not be arbiter!
Tindoiimu: ...You'll regret it.
Pang: I already regret too much.
Pang: Get out of the way!
Yao: It's over.
Yao: You!!
Pang: Everything I just saw, who know...
Pang: It was you!
Yao: Seems like you're choosing to betray me yet again.
Pang: Choice... you talk about choice, and yet... you chose to use me for your benefit, to participate in the tournament!
Yao: ……
Pang: Yao! Please, make me understand... If you hate me so much, why would you save me, and then harm me once again today!?
Yao: ...I thought you would change.
Pang: Change?
Yao: I thought, after all these years on the road, you would have realized what is right... you would join me, stand by my side.
Yao: And yet...
Yao: And yet you hide away in some lake, in the middle of nowhere, like some frightened rabbit!
Pang: You know nothing! I was living in constant regret, constant torment... Maple Lake saved me! I learned there the errors of my ways!
Pang: And I learned there that this world still has much beauty left in it, beauty that I needed to rediscover for myself!
Yao: Nonsense, all of it! If this world is so beautiful, then... then...
Yao: Why did my comrades all have to die!?
Yao: Who killed them!? Huh!?
Pang: Ah...
Yao: It was this damn Alliance! That's who! This useless, disgusting world!
Yao: But the one who really killed them, the most ignorant, useless one of all...
Yao: Was me!
Yao: Look at these things! These are what killed my comrades! I keep them shackled here on my own body to remind me of that, every day!
Yao: I'll never forget all of that vengeance! I'll never forget them!
Yao: That's why I have to finish what I've started, I have to destroy this corruption at the source! I must bring true justice to this wretched Alliance!
Pang: No! That is not justice!
Pang: Yao, I understand your pain, and yet... your desires are self-serving!
Yao: What?
Pang: Look around you, is this the true justice you desire!?
Pang: How can you look at all of these innocent people and talk about justice!?
Yao: I never wanted to be a hero! From the moment I set out on this path, I was prepared to take on my crimes... As I am, a criminal.
Pang: Yao...
Yao: Enough, there's nothing left to talk about!
Yao: Who will die here today!?
Pang: Gyagh!
Yao: Hmph. Why do you talk of justice and fight with such hesitation? Do you underestimate me?
Pang: Gngh... gah... This is all I must do... to stop you...
Pang: Chieftain! Run away from here!
Yao: Scoundrels!
Yao: Get out of here!
Yao: Damnit!!
Pang: Ungh... Yao...
